OL,3,CMcArthur 'confident' ahead of key vote
OL,4,Con assisted dying bill at Holyrood
OL,6,FIf a majority of MSPs back the
OL,7,FAssisted Dying for Terminally Ill
OL,8,FAdults (Scotland) Bill on Tuesday
OL,9,Fevening, more detailed scrutiny will
OL,10,Fbe carried out, with the legislation
OL,11,Falso opened up to other MSPs to put
OL,12,Fforward amendments, ahead of a final
OL,13,Fvote at Holyrood before it could
OL,14,Fbecome law.
OL,16,FBut arguing that the majority of the
OL,17,Fpublic support such a change, Mr
OL,18,FMcArthur insisted it "would be pretty
OL,19,Fdifficult to justify" voting down the
OL,20,FBill and not taking it forward for
OL,21,Famendments.
