OL,6,FBut he added: "As we get to Tuesday
OL,7,Fthere is a recognition, even among
OL,8,Fsome who still have reservations, that
OL,9,Fwe can't afford not to engage in the
OL,10,Fdetailed scrutiny of potential changes
OL,11,Fto this Bill that might address the
OL,12,Fconcerns they have."
OL,14,FWhile his legislation originally
OL,15,Fproposed allowing eligible Scots with
OL,16,Fa terminal illness to seek an assisted
OL,17,Fdeath from the age of 16, Mr McArthur
OL,18,Fannounced recently if the Bill
OL,19,Fprogresses he will change that to 18.
